<p>GDP growth: 4.3% GDP: $67bn (PPP: $132bn) Inflation: 4.3% Population: 14.6m GDP per head: $4,610 (PPP: $9,040)</p>

<p>Healthy oil receipts and lending from China have allowed the administration of Rafael Correa, a left-wing populist, to support growth through government spending. Although Mr Correa's popularity is declining, a fragmented opposition offers little alternative. Heavy state control and regulatory instability will deter all but the most intrepid investors.</p>

<p>To watch: Airborne. A new international airport will open in 2012, as Mariscal Sucre airport in Quito gives way to a modern facility 15km to the north-east.</p>

